content.description:
Super fun off-width that you can essentially climb as a lay-back. I have no idea where the crux it. The whole thing was just so exciting and scary, but in retrospect not that bad. Looks like it would only take 6" cams near the top, but there are some smaller cracks buried deep inside you can get some 2" cams and such in.

You'll know it when you see it.
Standard rack to 5" (although you can seriously get away with 4"). Anchors at the top.

climbs.name: You Rascal Me I Rascal You

content.description:
This puppy only has 2 bolts, but don't let that stop you. Stick clip the first bolt and then you only have one more and the anchors. Unfortunately (or more like fortunately) it gets tough after the first bolt to the end. Super fun delicate crimpy moves to the top. So good!

Just right of Rat Mother Crack.
2 bolts, and top anchors.
Sunny in the morning. Home to an impressive off-width, that you can sort of climb as a lay-back. Still, fun to shove yourself into that chimney near the end. Granite.
